name: Michaela DePrince
summary: The ballet community is mourning the loss of Michaela DePrince, a trailblazing ballerina who died at the age of 29. DePrince, who was born in Sierra Leone and adopted by an American family, began her dance career as a child and quickly rose to prominence. She became a principal dancer with the Boston Ballet in 2012 and made history as the first black woman to hold the position. DePrince was also a vocal advocate for diversity and inclusion in the ballet world, and she used her platform to speak out against racism and discrimination. Her death has been met with shock and sadness from the ballet community and beyond, with many expressing their admiration for her talent, resilience, and unwavering spirit. The cause of her death has not been disclosed.

name: Jared Isaacman
summary: SpaceX has successfully launched its Polaris Dawn mission, which includes billionaire Jared Isaacman and a crew of private astronauts. This is the first private spacewalk, where Isaacman ventured outside the SpaceX capsule hundreds of miles above Earth. The mission aims to advance human spaceflight and support future scientific research. Isaacman, who was born in New Jersey and is Jewish, is the founder of Shift4 Payments and has a keen interest in space exploration. The Polaris Dawn crew's successful spacewalk marks a significant milestone in the commercialization of space travel, paving the way for future private missions and expanding our understanding of space.
